cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.PL 

This paper discusses a new paradigm for database systems that leverages the actor abstraction for modularity and scalability. It also discusses software engineering challenges and the need for database system features to reduce bugs and programming effort. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
